posts.html:
Green-tech can be an oxymoron, tech has always been destructive in some way, the first life-changing technology was fire. And since then, all technologies that were life-changing for human beings relied on fire or in modern terms electricity or energy.

Electricity is fire under microscopic control.

Now, technology is important for human beings, because it frees us our valuable time, and brings us comfortable lives.

The issue rises when technology is used greedily, burning a lot of firewood will have as result the extinction of a forest and creates negative disequilibrium in the ecosystem.

In the same manner, burning a lot a fossil fuel creates a bad disequilibrium because the amount of CO2 released is way above the capacity of the flora to absorb, and thus disturbing the fragile moderate climate we have on earth.

Temperatures rise is now not something we expect in the future, but is already a current reality, as graphs and data already show.

The disequilibrium expected by scientists will results in hothouse earth by the end of the century, if nothing changes.

This situation will impact you directly at your old age if you are now young, and will necessarily impact your future children and grandchildren that you will love more than yourself.

The truth is bitter.

But they say that truth is bitter in the beginning and sweet in the end, but lies are sweet in the beginning but bitter in the end.

Let's face this challenge together by being more responsible ourselves, and sparking the conversation with our neighbors and relatives and push the rulers to implement new rulings that defend our habitat.

Farewell,

Now is the time to act, as many people suffer already for an increase in pollution, tree planting help mitigates the risks, and sequestrate carbon as well as reset the water flows.

I started this fundraising campaign to help build these tree planting types of projects around the world, and I'm looking for anyone who can help.

Please donate to my campaign -- anything you can give is a huge help.
100% of the money will be used to build tree planting projects, and when they’re complete, Clean green Morocco will send us photos and GPS coordinates so we can see the exact community we helped.

Thank you

posts.html:
It is easy to set up, a backyard tree nursery will take you a few weekends spent setting it up.

If you have space and live in a place of the city where you can afford to plant trees in your neighborhood, you should think about it.

To grow trees from seeds never cease to amaze, the seemingly inert seed, that suddenly becomes a small seedling with few leaves is something that brings me joy every time.

You know you are doing a truly productive thing with your time, you will learn more about your food, about botany, the cycles of life, and even about yourself. It will teach you to be patient and resourceful. As well as grateful for all the food we find stacked in the supermarkets.

I use plastic bottles to make the pots. And I bring good soil from a forest or a garden nearby. It is fairly easy, and it demands the only handwork.

I know not everybody will try to do make his nursery, and that other people are specialists growing thousands of trees. My goal is to inspire a stranger to an act that we forget to do in our busy modern lives.

Find the time, do it, plant the tree,
Farewell,

posts.html:
Increase in Speed, Power, and Control, are what seems to motivate human beings in their works of creation.

To build a world where nature is controled, where seemingly random patterns of nature are replaced with squares and circles. Resources, animals and ecological systems with numbers, and to squeeze out the maximum of resources from earth in the minimum amount of time so that we can have time to enjoy a short life.

Well let me tell you my friend that no amount of ressources extracted and food ingested will make us full, if our hearts are not grateful, thankful and appreciative of what we have, regardless of their quantity.

Competition is the result of a story of separation we tell ourselves. That we are separate from other creations, that we are an entity that can somehow survive on its own without any external help.

This seems a metaphore that is running widly these last times, specially in big cities where people are now remembered by there care giver "the state" by numbers, are dealing everyday with survival ressources ( food, shelter, energy, ... ) in form of numbers in the bill. And somehow seem to forgot where all these came from.

Focused toward fleeting materialistic goals that as long as they are achieved no longer procure nor provide the inner joy and happiness that we long for.

The heart longs for eternity, for its essence is eternal, that is why we never can get in peace with the idea that we will die and disappear one day. For the heart knows it belongs to eternity.

To reconnect to our hearts, is the way to uniting us to others with what is commonly shared. There only we can build systems that are sustainable because they take care of the place of every

We naturally have came across this situation, and most of us are surviving the day to day life, for it is way complicated to question the systems we work (play) on. IIt is indeed complicated when we see around us, the catastrophes of homeless people, and abondoned man and women, in the midst of very rich cities.

One thing that surprised me the most is how low is the number of abondoned people in the far unknown villages, compared to the cities where poverty seems to be more prevalent.

Weirdly enough, ecology comes from the word village. The village is the place where human lives and natural forces comes in encounter. And they seem to have lived in balance until the last century.

How to find the equilibrium and balance between technology and ecology is one of the major challenges of this century, to not fall into the clever but sometimes unwise solutions of technologists that think that all can be solved with numbers, nor the panic of the environmentalists that would like to stop all technology advancements.

Hard balance indeed when it looks almost as a combat between heaven and hell. Or knowledge of good and evil and ignorance. Where every party thinks it is working for the good. Technologists thinking that technology is all that will save us, and environmentalists thinking that technology will bring the last on earth and thus on human life on earth.
